The paper deals with compressed sensing theory and Lasso programs, which are commonly studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of numerical simulations suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The concept of instability in parameter choice is a novel contribution, which may also be of interest to the statistical learning (cs.SI) sub-category.
